    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="317" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName>Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1525.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                        August</hi> 25, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch, No. 1031, of the 10th of
                            August, relative to the depredations committed by the Sea King in the
                            sea of Okhotsk, has been received. No representations and no farther
                            information upon the subject have been communicated to this
                            department.</p>
                <p>You are at liberty to exercise your own discretion as to the expediency
                            of postponing action in the matter.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
